(18, 'The Mother\'s International School', 1956, 'public', 'cbse', 'co-ed', 'The school was founded on 23 April 1956 by founder Shri Surendra Nath Jauhar \"Faquir\", with the blessings of The Mother, Mirra Alfassa, a spiritualist, the spiritual partner and collaborator of Sri Aurobindo.\r\n\r\nThe school\'s motto \"More True, Forever More True\" was given by the Mirra Alfassa, known as the Mother, and the school\'s emblem portrays a bird in flight rising towards heaven. When asked about the date of the school\'s opening, the Mother replied \"23456\". And as the only possible date was 23 April 1956, it was this day that the school first opened.\r\n\r\nWhen the school started out, a batch (or a grade) was of about 15 children, but today a batch has 180 students. The school has three wings, the Pre-Primary, Primary and Secondary. The pre-primary program of The Mother\'s International School replaced Mira Nursery, a pre-primary school it previously shared campus with.', 'The school teaches four languages: English, Hindi, Sanskrit and French. It also teaches mathematics, science and social studies till Class 10. There are three main streams for study beyond Class 10: Science, Commerce and Humanities.\r\n\r\nFor classes 1 and 2, there is only 1-3 teachers and they teach all the subjects; in the 3rd grade and above, there is a different teacher for each subject, with one class teacher. The student/teacher ratio is approximately 1 teacher for every 62 students.\r\n\r\nIn 2001, Outlook\'s \"C-Fore Best School Survey\" has ranked MIS as one of the top 10 schools in India, and the best school in Delhi', 'Students are allowed to choose extracurricular activities that they are interested in, including art and crafts, classical dance, a range of sports activities, vocal and instrumental music.\r\n\r\nThe school also offers a range of facilities for those interested in pottery and clay modeling, carpentry, drama, quizzing, yoga, taekwondo, gymnastics, s.education, music (instrumental as well as vocal) and art groups. The school actively hosts inter-school competitions for the above.\r\n\r\nEach year, inter-house competitions are held in the school as well - including the Bag drama, oral interpretation, poem festivals, and debates. The school also holds a talent show on 23 April, which is also the school foundation day.', 'The school has an annual magazine, Navchetna (\"new thoughts\" in Sanskrit). The magazine contains poems and articles submitted by the students themselves. On the school\'s 60th Anniversary, it was themed upon the spaces in the school which students, teachers and alumni could relate to. This magazine is considered to be very special by the students of the school, as no matter how ostentatiously or simply the articles are written, they are extremely poignant. The editorial board of the Navchetna is changed annually for all the four languages that are there in the magazine: Hindi, English, Sanskrit and French. The English editorial board plays a major role in creating a framework for the magazine.', 2223, 100, 10, 'the mother\'s international school aurbindo ', 'This is delhi\'s no.1 school', 103),
(23, 'Vasant Valley School, Delhi', 1990, 'private', 'cbse', 'co-ed', 'Vasant Valley School, New Delhi was established in 1990. It is a self-financing day school affiliated to CBSE. It was ranked fourth among the day schools in India in the EducationWorld-C fore Indiaâ€™s Most Respected Schools Survey 2011. The schoolâ€™s 8 acre campus has modern infrastructure and fully equipped laboratories. Whilst high academic achievement is a priority, the school aims to create a community of well rounded individuals, where a spirit of cooperation and mutual respect exists among the students and teachers. The school organizes several activities throughout the year with an emphasis on the studentâ€™s intellectual and emotional growth.', 'Established by the India Today Group, Vasant Valley is a prep-12 school. Students of classes XI and XII prepare for the All India Senior School Certificate Examination (A.I.S.S.C.E.) conducted by the Central Board of Secondary Education. The school offers eighteen different subject choices at the elective level. Each student is required to take four elective subjects along with English core.\r\n\r\nThe school also offers and encourages extra-curricular activities like sports, debating and quizzing and has a good history of students participating in prestigious debates throughout the country.', 'Vasant Valley School, Delhi is ranked among the top coeducational day schools in India by leading education surveys.', 'A student must be of a minimum three years of age for admission into preschool. To apply under the general category, parents must produce the following documents:\r\n\r\nResidence proof (any one of the documents must be produced): ration card, voter ID card, telephone bill, electricity bill, water bill, passport.Childâ€™s birth certificate For first born child, affidavit by parents confirming that the child is their first born.\r\n\r\nFees: Quarterly tuition fee approx Rs. 22,625 â€“ 30,975', 1300, 50, 10, 'vasant valley school', 'This page give info about vasant valley school', 109),
(24, 'Heritage Xperiential Learning School, Gurgaon', 2002, 'private', 'cbse', 'co-ed', 'The Heritage School, Gurgaon was promoted in 2002 by N.C. Jain, chairman of the school. It is an English medium co-educational school affiliated with the Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE), New Delhi and offers classes from nursery to higher secondary.\r\n\r\nThe school maintains a high faculty-student ratio to facilitate individual attention and better learning, besides investing a lot of time and resources in teacher training. According to a school spokesperson, â€œOur endeavour is to help children develop their full potential. A tremendous amount of care and nurturing goes into physical, mental, and cognitive teaching methodology which steadily unfolds the childâ€™s true and inherent potential.â€', 'The school is affiliated with CBSE and the academic system is divided into three levels:\r\n\r\nJunior Programme (nursery to grade III) â€“ The Junior Programme adopts inquiry and exploration as vehicles for learning and aims to make learning a fun experience.\r\n\r\nMiddle Programme (grade IV to VII) â€“  The teaching-learning experience in the Middle Programme is a balanced amalgamation of hands on project work and analyses of experiences to construct concepts, knowledge and skill sets modeled around Project Based Learning (PBL).\r\n\r\nSenior Programme (grade VIII to XII) â€“ The Senior Programme adopts a dialogic, participative pedagogy and students are constantly encouraged and empowered to be self-directed and accept responsibility for learning.\r\n\r\nThe Heritage School is one of the few schools in the country that provides education to differently abled children.\r\n\r\nExtracurricular: The school encourages a variety of co-curricular activities such as music, dance, drama, painting, literature, film and sculpture. Students are also encouraged to engage themselves in sports such as basket ball, football, hockey, tennis, badminton, cricket and swimming.', 'The Heritage School is one of the few schools in the country that provides education to differently abled children.', 'Registration and application forms can be downloaded from the school website. Minimum age criterion for admission to nursery is three years plus as on April 1 of the year of admission. Admission to nursery is on the basis of an interaction/interview with the school authorities. Admissions to class I to X are on the basis of performance in the written test and interview. Admissions to class XI and XII are based on the class X board results conducted by CBSE and any other equivalent board exams and interview of the child.\r\n\r\nFees: Annual fee for nursery is Rs. 1, 18,000.', 3300, 350, 20, 'Heritage Xperiential Learning School', 'This page give info about Heritage Xperiential Learning School', 110),
(25, 'The Valley School, Bangalore', 1978, 'private', 'icse', 'co-ed', 'The Valley School, established in 1978, is one of the five schools of the Krishnamurti Foundation India. The Valley School is based on the teachings of the eminent philosopher and a great thinker of our times, Jiddu Krishnamurti. It is located in a 120 acres campus to the south of Bangalore, in a picturesque valley with undulating hills and farms and with a reserve forest on the fringe. The Valley School is a coeducational, English medium day-school affiliated to CISCE (Council for the Indian School Certificate Examinations), New Delhi. The school has been successful in implementing an â€˜Open Classroomâ€™ where vertical groups of children from class I to IV can learn together. The open classroom not only allows for a variety of foundational skills to be explored but also provides the opportunity for students to direct their own learning.\r\n\r\nIt hasa student strength of about 365 and teacher strength of about 60. The school believes that the learning can take place, if one can avoid the division of school activities as academic non- academic, and separate them from day to day living.It also believes that grouping children basedon classes and grades and expecting all of them to learn at the same level and pace is inappropriate.', 'The lower school is run based on Jiddu Krishnamurti\'s philosophies, where teachers and students are given freedom and flexibility. At the lower schools, the students are encouraged to think and derive at answers through guidance and correction. Along with a standard curriculum of science and humanities, extra-curricular activities are encouraged. Tests and examinations are kept to a minimum where there are no official \"annual exam\" till Grade 9. When a student reaches Grade 9 it will be the first time the students writes an exam conducted by the school.\r\n\r\nHigher classes follow a standard ICSE curriculum, where they appear for a nationwide public board examination at the end of class 10. Class 12 students appear for the ISC examinations conducted by the same board. The School has had a 100% Pass percentage in both 10th and 12th since the batch of 1999.', 'Interactions between teacher and student are informal and based on Jiddu Krishnamurtiâ€™s philosophy that \"Learning cannot happen when there is fear\". Freedom with responsibility is emphasized from an early age, and rewards and punishments are kept to a minimum. Students are encouraged to direct their own learning.', '', 350, 30, 120, 'The Valley School Bangalore', 'This page give info about The Valley School Bangalore', 111),
(26, 'Smt. Sulochanadevi Singhania School', 1968, 'private', 'icse', 'co-ed', 'Smt. Sulochanadevi Singhania School is located in lush green surroundings of Jekegram in the heart of the city of Thane. The premier institution was started in 1969 by Shri. Gopalkrishna Singhania. Over the years, it has grown to accommodate children from all walks of life and today, it has 5100 students on roll from KG to class XII. The school is an unaided linguistic minority institution run by the Smt. Sulochanadevi Singhania Trust. Air Cdre. Vijaypat Singhania is the Chairman and has on its Board of Governors, eminent professionals from the field of management and education.', '2016 ICSE Results\r\nSchool average : 91%\r\n492 students took the examinations and 67% of them scored 90% or over.\r\n\r\nThe number of students who scored 100%:[when?] Mathematics â€“ 20\r\nScience â€“ 3\r\nHome science 5\r\nCommercial applications â€“ 14\r\nTechnical drawing â€“ 4\r\nComputer applications â€“ 88\r\n\r\nThe school was ranked Mumbaiâ€™s No. 1 day co-educational school by the Hindustan Times Top School Survey 2015\r\n\r\nThe school was ranked the countryâ€™s No. 1, the stateâ€™s No. 1 and Mumbaiâ€™s No. 1 day co-educational school in the Education World India school rankings 2015 for its efforts towards an holistic approach to education, based on a survey conducted by C-fore for Education World.', 'The school is an unaided linguistic minority institution run by the Smt. Sulochanadevi Singhania Trust. Air Cdre. Vijaypat Singhania is the Chairman and has on its Board of Governors, eminent professionals from the field of management and education.', 'IMPORTANT GUIDELINES :\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe School believes in absolute transparency with regard to its admissions.\r\nProspective parents are requested to check up the School Website from time to time, to ensure that they do not miss the dates.\r\nAll admissions to the school are online.\r\nAny wrong information on the application form will amount to disqualification.\r\nAdmissions are based on random sampling.\r\nRecommendation/request letters regarding admission will amount to rejection of the application. Kindly do not meet the school authorities regarding such matters.\r\nThe school does not accept any favors, by way of donations or capitation fees. We advise the parents to stay away from people who promise admissions in exchange for money.\r\nThe Admission Committee reserves its rights on issues regarding admission.', 1000, 89, 13, 'Smt. Sulochanadevi Singhania School', 'This page give info about Smt. Sulochanadevi Singhania School', 112),
(27, 'Step by Step, Noida', 1992, 'private', 'cbse', 'co-ed', 'Step By Step School located in Noida, was established in the year 1992 with a vision of providing quality education to students. The school is an English medium co-educational school affiliated to Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE). Step By Step School is dedicated to provide world class educational facilities to the students and offers education from classes play group â€“ class XII. To ensure the complete development of the children, Step By Step School encourages the students to take part in various co-curricular activities held in school such as music, dance, arts and sports. The campus of Step By Step School is well equipped with the modern infrastructural facilities such as spacious ventilated class rooms with the latest teaching aids, rich library, state-of-the-art computer labs, science labs and play ground.\r\nThe school is synonymous with quality and is highly regarded as a school that provides a loving environment where young children are watched over by a committed and nurturing faculty. The school has an excellent student teacher ratio and a creative curriculum which focuses on learning through activity and play.', 'SENIOR\r\nSenior School Years â€“ Classes 9 to 12\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSuccess during the years of Senior School is vital to the future goals and aspirations of all our students and their families. Our curriculum is geared to honours level academic courses and offers a range of 20 electives at class XI and XII in the Central Board of Secondary Education.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nOur students can also choose to pursue the international curriculum - the International General Certificate of Secondary Education IGCSE (Class X), and the International Baccalaureate (IB) Diploma (Class XII).\r\n\r\n ', 'The school is synonymous with quality and is highly regarded as a school that provides a loving environment where young children are watched over by a committed and nurturing faculty. The school has an excellent student teacher ratio and a creative curriculum which focuses on learning through activity and play.', 'The information about the admission is given school website', 2449, 54, 21, 'Step by Step Noida', 'This page give info about Step by Step Noida', 113),
(28, 'Mallya Aditi International School', 1984, 'private', 'icse', 'co-ed', 'Named after Vijay Mallya â€“ the UB Group chairman and member of parliament â€“ Mallya Aditi International School (MAIS), Bangalore was established in 1984 conceptualised by the Ujwal educational trust, led by well-known educationists Anne Warrior and Geetha Narayanan who over the past 28 years have changed the conventional norms of teaching, putting in place an integrated system of learning.\r\n\r\nThis private co-educational prep-12 school committed to academic excellence is forth-ranked among day schools all India in the latest EducationWorld-C fore India School Ranking Survey 2012.\r\n\r\nThe schoolâ€™s mission is to offer its students a global education delivered by internationally trained faculty and equip them with necessary skill sets to transform them into confident innovators.\r\n', 'Examinations are held at the end of each academic year for grades 6, 7 and 8. For grades 9 and 10, a choice between the Indian Certificate of Secondary Education (ICSE) and the International General Certificate of Secondary Education (IGCSE) is offered. For grades 11 and 12, a choice between the Indian School Certificate (ISC) and the Advanced International Certificate of Education (AICE) is offered. IGCSE and AICE are conducted by the University of Cambridge International Examinations â€“ CIE. Week-long internships are also compulsory in the 12th grade.\r\n\r\n Aditi has received recognition for the excellence of its faculty.[2] The school has ISC topper for year 2019 with 100% score. ', 'In 2005, the school was awarded the Cambridge Fellowship by the University of Cambridge in England, in recognition of academic excellence among schools offering Cambridge qualifications. Only 20 secondary schools in the world have received this fellowship. In early 2005, Aditi won the Intel Award for the Best Integration of Technology in Education 2004, from a pool of India\'s best schools.\r\n\r\nAditi is one of the two or three schools chosen worldwide by the University of Cambridge to be prototypes in an experimental science exam (where the practical paper is completed through computer simulation). These schools were chosen based on their academic record. The results of the students in the board exams will decide whether or not the experimental paper will come into practice.', 'Please read the FAQ section (below) before emailing the Admissions Officer with an enquiry. You are also invited to explore this website for additional information.\r\n\r\nYou need to fix an appointment with the Admissions Officer if you want a tour of the school.\r\n\r\nProspective parents are encouraged to visit the school on Elementary School Open Day on July 21, 2019 (9 a.m. to 12 noon).\r\n\r\nParents are advised not to have any dealings with people or websites claiming that they can obtain admission. \r\n\r\nWe DO NOT work with agents or intermediaries. The school DOES NOT have a management quota for admissions.\r\n\r\nAttempts to influence/pressurise admission decisions through letters and/or calls on behalf of applicants will not be appreciated.\r\n\r\nThere are generally no vacancies in Stds.2-8. Should any arise, details will be published on the website after May 15. In these classes, preference will be given to siblings of students currently enrolled in the school.\r\n\r\nThe Principal does not, as mandated by the Ujwal Trust, play any role in the admission process.', 650, 40, 12, 'Mallya Aditi International School', 'This page give info about Mallya Aditi International School', 114),
(29, 'Inventure Academy, Bangalore', 2005, 'private', 'icse', 'co-ed', 'Inventure Academy is a Pre K â€“ Grade 12 International School, established in 2005, located on Whitefield-Sarjapur Road, and ranked among the top ten co-ed day schools in India, and third in Bangalore and Karnataka by the Education World C-Fore Survey, 2017. Inventure Academyâ€™s unique curriculum, which equips children with 21st Century life skills and is focused on their holistic development, with the expectation that each child will flourish in academics, athletics, and other co-curricular spheres. Inventure Academy offers Pre K-12 curriculum, based on guidelines from IGCSE, A/AS Levels from CIE and CISCE (Council for the Indian School Certificate Examination). The school has affiliation with both examining boards.', 'Inventure Academy follows the curriculum of the Council for the Indian School Certificate Examinations (CISCE), New Delhi and Cambridge International Examinations (CIE), United Kingdom.\r\n\r\nThe curriculum of the school fosters new ways of thinking, considering and developing ideas. The curriculum is highly experiential, contextual, activity-oriented, and based on multidisciplinary teaching approaches.\r\n\r\nExtracurricular: Inventure Academyâ€™s co-curricular activities range from sports to creative arts, to field trips and outbound trips, community outreach programs, and annual literary competitions, known as Tournaments of Minds. The school also encourages its students to participate in a wide range of unique initiatives such as Changemaker and Makerspace.', 'Inventure Academy is one of the three select schools in Bangalore to be part of Round Square, a not-for-profit network of schools in 40 countries across five continents, that share a passion for experiential learning built around six IDEALS of Learning: Democracy, Environmentalism, Adventure, Leadership, and Service.', 'Admissions at Inventure Academy are open throughout the year depending on the availability of seats. For the academic year of 2017-2018 admissions are open from pre-K to grade 12. The fee structure is available on request.', 2532, 70, 37, 'Inventure Academy Bangalore', 'This page give info about Inventure Academy Bangalore', 115),
(30, 'Cathedral and John Connon School', 1860, 'private', 'icse', 'co-ed', 'The Cathedral and John Connon School was founded by the Anglo-Scottish Education Society in Mumbai, in 1860. It began as a humble establishment when Bishop Harding and the Cathedral Chaplain decided to start a small grammar school for boys and one for girls. According to the Education World-C fore Survey of Schools 2012, the school has been ranked as Indiaâ€™s third best day school. In the 1960s, the boys and girls schools were merged to successfully solve the schoolâ€™s financial and logistical problems.\r\n\r\nThe school now has 5 sections in Mumbai. Its pre-primary section established in 2002 is housed within the compounds of the St. Thomas Cathedral, Mumbai. The infant school is at Malabar Hill, the junior school at M.G. Road, the middle school at Maharishi Dadichi Marg, and the senior school at P.T. Marg.', 'The Cathedral & John Connon School is affiliated with the Council for the Indian School Certificate Examinations (CISCE), and its students appear for the Council\'s ISC, IB (Grade 12) and ICSE (Grade 10) examinations. English is the medium of instruction. Hindi is taught as a second language and Marathi or Sanskrit are taught as third languages. The school\'s students have performed well at the ICSE and ISC examinations and the school has maintained a 100% pass-rate.\r\n\r\nCollege Board\'s Advanced Placement program has been conducted in the school since June, 2004. Talented students, who would otherwise be uninterested in a mainstream classroom, are offered the chance to pursue accelerated learning (college-level) courses in subjects including English, Calculus (AB and BC), Physics, Biology, Computers, World History, Chemistry and Economics.[9] The school is the only AP Examination Center in Western India.\r\n\r\nFor the ISC course (consisting of grades 11 and 12) the school divided its student body into three streams: Commerce, Science, and the Humanities. However, as of 2008 this is no longer required and students now have the option of either choosing a particular stream or choosing subjects from different streams.\r\n\r\nStudents achieving distinctions (above 80% per term in Senior School) throughout the year become eligible for the Honours Prize for that year. Those who achieve fifteen points on a complicated scoring system, at any time after Grade 8, are awarded the Scholar\'s Badge. There are rarely more than three recipients in any given year.', 'The school now has 5 sections in Mumbai. Its pre-primary section established in 2002 is housed within the compounds of the St. Thomas Cathedral, Mumbai. The infant school is at Malabar Hill, the junior school at M.G. Road, the middle school at Maharishi Dadichi Marg, and the senior school at P.T. Marg.', 'Applications for Std. II to IX are accepted at the security desk from 1st September to 15th December. Applications are to be addressed to the Principal. Kindly mention the class you are interested in and your contact numbers and email address very clearly. A copy each of the birth certificate and the latest progress report of the child is to be attached with the application.\r\n\r\nIncomplete applications will be disqualified.\r\nThe Last date for submission is 15th December. Late applications will not be entertained.\r\nPlease mention your email address and contact numbers clearly. In case a vacancy occurs, the school office will contact you.', 3000, 75, 10, 'Cathedral and John Connon School', 'This page give info about Cathedral and John Connon School', 116),
(31, 'Sanskriti School, Chanakyapuri, Delhi', 1998, 'public', 'cbse', 'co-ed', 'Sanskriti School is a recognized integrated co-educational school with affiliation to CBSE, which offers education from classes nursery to XII. Located in the diplomatic area of Chanakyapuri in New Delhi, the school has been consistently ranked as one of the top schools in Delhi and countrywide as well. According to the Education World-C fore Survey of Schools 2012, the school has been ranked at the No. 10 position in the day school category of the India School Rankings. The school was established by the Civil Services Society, formed by the wives of the civil servants belonging to the various branches of Government of India with the aim to fulfill a need in the city of Delhi for education for children of officers of All India and Allied Services and Defence Personnel coming on transfer. The design aesthetic for the school follows a contemporary modern Indian sensibility. The facade treatments for all the buildings are in brick tiles and shell roofs which are in blue glazed tiles. The Sanskriti School also runs a parallel school called Umang, where underprivileged children are provided free education. Children living in Sanjay Basti, a slum behind the school, are the main students who attended Umang.', 'At school, the students hone their academic and extra-curricular skills to prepare for their journey into the world outside the protective environs of the school. Innovative and effective teaching methodologies are used by the teachers with a focus on the constantly changing educational pedagogy which enhances academic achievement. Apart from skills and knowledge, due attention is also paid to inculcating values which will stand them in good stead in life. Our unique system of instituting a class teacherâ€™s interactive period every morning is used to ensure that our students become sensitive and sensible citizens of the world. We are indeed proud that our senior students not only prove their mettle in the academic arena in India and abroad but also distinguish themselves with their strength of character.', 'The school was established by the Civil Services Society, formed by the wives of the civil servants belonging to the various branches of Government of India with the aim to fulfill a need in the city of Delhi for education for children of officers of All India and Allied Services and Defence Personnel coming on transfer.\r\n\r\nAccording to the Hindustan Times, Sanskriti School was ranked the best school in Central Delhi in 2009 and second best in 2010. In 2015, it was ranked as the 6th best school in Delhi and the second best in Central Delhi. This school has also got ranked at top 6th position in Delhi at top10pick.in website.', 'The information is given on the school website', 1200, 112, 8, 'Sanskriti School Chanakyapuri  Delhi', 'This page give info about  Sanskriti School Chanakyapuri  Delhi', 117),
(32, 'The Shri Ram School, Aravali', 1988, 'private', 'icse', 'co-ed', 'The ShriRamSchool, Delhi is a progressive, child-centered, co-educational private school, committed to providing quality education to all its pupils. Established in the year 1988, the school has two campuses in the Delhi and NCR region, offering a unique and alternative educational experience to children from nursery to class XII.\r\n\r\nThe mission of The Shri Ram School is to provide each student a diverse education in a safe, supportive environment that promotes sound values, self discipline, motivation and excellence in learning.', 'The school offers various study options to its students. The school is affiliated to the Council for the IndianSchool Certificate Examination, Delhi. This council is approved and recognised by the All India Boards of Secondary Education. The council has two public examinations- the Indian Certificate of Secondary Education (ICSE) at the end of class X and the Indian School Certificate (ISC) at the end of class XII.\r\n\r\nThe school is also affiliated with the Geneva-based International Baccalaureate Organisation and offers International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme (IBDP) which is a 2 year course with an examination at the end of the class XII. It is also a learning centre for National Institute for Open Schooling (NIOS).\r\n\r\nAfter completing class X, students can choose between ISC or IB.\r\n\r\nA Special Education Needs programme (SEN) is also in place to provide inclusive educational opportunities to children with special needs.\r\n\r\nExtra-curricular activities like sport, dance, music, art, clay, drama and hobby classes run parallel to the academic curriculum.', 'The children of Class XI take part each year in Socially Useful Productive Work (SUPW) during which they spend a week in a village, experiencing every aspect of village life and contributing to it. Prior to the trip, the village is asked for a wish list and the children offer physical labour to fulfil that need. For example, the students have constructed a road, built a shed in the cremation ground and a completely cemented basketball court - acquiring the skills needed to do so. The students work with the villagers, visit their homes and share their food thus gaining a true understanding of the challenges and strengths of rural India\r\n\r\nThis is one of the top school in Gurugram.', 'The admission process for LKG starts from the month of January, and children who are three and a half years of age can apply for admissions. Admission for other classes is on roll-over basis and is open throughout the year subject to vacancies. There is a formal advertisement that is placed in leading daily newspapers. The application form is available online at the school website and also at the campus.\r\n\r\nOnce the forms are received an elaborate point system and draw of lots/lottery (as per the guidelines stipulated by the Delhi education department) determines the students in the first list and the second (waiting) list. A third list is also taken out if the need arises.\r\n\r\nAdmissions close by March 31st each year.', 1600, 50, 15, 'The Shri Ram School  Aravali', 'This page give info about The Shri Ram School Aravali', 118),
(33, 'Vidyashilp Academy', 1998, 'private', 'icse', 'co-ed', 'Vidyashilp Academy, Bangalore was founded on July 6, 1998 by Ravindra Vithlani, who was not an educationist by qualification but belonged to the marketing field. His wife Hansa Vithlani had founded Vidyasagar a couple of years ago and in 1982, she started Vidyaniketan School. The education concept promoted by the school was not textbook based, instead it emphasized on intellectual development, practical knowledge and knowledge gained by interaction. Vidyashilp Academy started with 12 teachers and 105 teachers and it now comprises 1740 students and 192 teaching staff, maintaining a teacher-student ratio of 1:9.\r\n\r\nThe school is referred to as first and most progressive school in the country. The school also represents evolution of excellence in the field of education. The schoolâ€™s academic initiatives function in a collaborative and dynamic environment in recognition to the childâ€™s ability to think. The schoolâ€™s main ingredients for moulding an excellent individual are canvas of social, moral and ethical values.\r\n\r\nIn 2005, Vidyashilpâ€™s first batch of 35 students passed the ICSE exams with flying colours.', 'Vidyashilp Academy follows Indian Certificate of Secondary Examinations (ICSE) curriculum, from Class I to X. The school also offers the Cambridge International General Certificate of Secondary Education (IGCSE) curriculum for students who wish to pursue it.\r\n\r\nThe school does not follow textbook approach of imparting education; rather multiple intelligence educational method is followed. From first grade to seventh grade there are no text books and the syllabus is authored by the teachers. From seventh grade onwards textbooks are used as referential resource. The classrooms are ICT enabled. The school organizes teacher induction programmes spread throughout the academic year.\r\n\r\nExtracurricular:\r\n\r\nVidyashilp Academy encourages every student to participate in atleast one sport so that the students specialize in atleast one activity of their choice. The school offers, skating, swimming, kho-kho, yoga, handball, throw ball, aerobics, chess and cricket.\r\n\r\nAlongside the regular curriculum, the school also provides balanced inputs through activities such as Shilp Encounter and Shilp Dew. These activities help to enhance the studentsâ€™ general awareness and knowledge about the surrounding local, national and global environment.', 'Vidyashilp Academy was nominated directly in the Engineering Watch Award 2013.\r\n\r\nVidyashilp Academy is consistently ranked among the best schools in India by leading education surveys.\r\n\r\n2017- Won 2nd place in UNESCO happy school video contest.\r\n\r\n2017- setting up of advanced learning Centre (for gifted children)) in collaboration with NIAS (national institute of advanced studies, IISC, Bangalore) \r\n\r\nContribution to the â€“ Happy Schools! A framework for learner well-being in the asia pacific drafted by UNESCO Bangkok 2015', 'The admission is solely based on entrance exam, studentâ€™s potential and marks scored in the previous class. The admission procedure completes in May but sometime it also depends on the availability of seats.\r\n\r\nFees-\r\n\r\nCISCE: Rs. 43000 per quarter (3 quarters)\r\n\r\nIGCSE: Rs. 83000 per quarter (3 quarters)', 1740, 192, 25, 'Vidyashilp Academy Bangalore', 'This page give info about Vidyashilp Academy Bangalore', 119),
(34, 'The School of KFI', 1973, 'private', 'icse', 'co-ed', 'The School-KFI, founded by J. Krishnamurti in 1973, is the third of the Krishnamurti schools in India and is known for sensitive and creative education in Chennaiâ€™s academic world.\r\n\r\nToday it is a full-fledged day boarding, co-educational school with students in junior, middle and senior schools and various distinctive programmes at all levels. The school has an ambience that has been crafted to facilitate meaningful interactions between adults and students.\r\n\r\nThe school works with the vision that a student who approaches the final years in school would have developed:\r\n\r\nA sense of integrity, dignity and confidence to face lifeâ€™s challenges\r\n\r\nA sensitivity to relate rightly to the earth and to all life\r\n\r\nAn ability to learn on oneâ€™s own and take responsibility for learning\r\n\r\nThe capacity to make choices of future activities in consonance with oneâ€™s deepest predilections\r\n\r\nThe intelligence to remain a sensitive human being with openness', 'Students learn all regular subjects through school. The school sees that all subjects are essentially interrelated and that the division of knowledge into subjects serves reasons of practicality. In learning each student must begin from where he or she is and not conform to a standard expectation; and it is for the teacher to nurture this growth in learning. All learning at school attempts to build the student\'s understanding of the subject and its relation to life. \r\n\r\nThe students of Classes 1 to 7 learn in mixed age groups at Junior School and Middle School. These learning groups are changed every year. The students of Classes  8 to 10 learn in same age groups as do students of Classes 11 and 12 who study different combinations of subjects.\r\n\r\nThe medium of instruction is English. The students learn both Tamil and Hindi till Class 8 and continue to study either one as an examination subject at Class 10.\r\n\r\nThe school understands that students learn in different ways and at different paces and adopts a variety of teaching-learning processes that allow students to approach learning with understanding. These processes are discussed among staff and reviewed and modified from time to time.\r\n\r\nStudents of all classes have field studies through day trips in junior school and three to ten day trips in middle and senior school. These move from nature walks and neighbourhood studies to historical and geographical studies to participating in the work of people in different parts of the country.', 'Today it is a full-fledged day boarding, co-educational school with students in junior, middle and senior schools and various distinctive programmes at all levels. The school has an ambience that has been crafted to facilitate meaningful interactions between adults and students.', 'The School KFI invites parents seeking to embark upon a journey of inquiry, not only for their children but also for themselves.', 400, 35, 10, 'The School of KFI', 'This page give info about The School of KFI Chennai', 120),
(35, 'Springdales School', 1984, 'private', 'cbse', 'co-ed', 'Run by the Springdales School society in New Delhi, the Springdales School Dhaula Kuan branch opened in 1984. The co-educational private school is a member of the National Progressive Schoolsâ€™ Conference and was ranked seventhamong day schools all India in the Education World-C fore Survey 2012 â€“ India School Rankings.\r\n\r\nSpringdales epitomises vibrancy and freshness, dovetailing much of the ethos of the new post-independence India into its educational program and philosophy. Privately managed, the school is a secular co-educational one integrating into its curriculum concern for the environment, the spirit of community service and international peace and brotherhood. The school integrates concepts of environmental concern and community service into their academic curriculum for the studentâ€™s overall development.\r\n\r\nThe school also has a well recognized Integrated special needs program for differently â€“ abled children and a special needs centre.', 'Springdales is known in educational circles for the innovative ideas and practices it has introduced into the educational process, and which now form part of the curriculum in many progressive schools of India.\r\n\r\nThe curriculum is multi-dimensional including an academic programme of high quality, a wide range of co-curricular activity, a comprehensive programme of sports and physical culture, training in manual skills and education for social awareness and action. The students participate in music, dance, drama and debate competitions and wherever they go they make an impact. The school itself hosts many contests in the field of poetry recitation, quizzing and science symposia during the school year. It is a point worth noting that in spite of the heavy programme of co-curricular activity our academic results are excellent and in the top range of schools anywhere in the country.', 'The school provides a pleasing learning environment with a spirit of sharing and caring and with close bonds between teachers and students. At Springdales, education is looked upon as a holistic learning experience to help children to develop those attributes and qualities of heart, head and hand which will make them self-reliant individuals and fine human beings, socially aware, compassionate and kind, having pride in their country and belief in the concept of global citizenship, people who are ready to work as agencies of change for building a more socially just and equitable society. ', 'The admission procedure is given on the school website', 1237, 90, 10, 'Springdales School', 'This page give info about Springdales School', 121),
(36, 'CHIREC Public School', 1989, 'private', 'cbse', 'co-ed', 'Founded in 1989, CHIREC School, Hyderabad is an English medium co-educational day school affiliated with the Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE), New Delhi, University of Cambridge InternationalExaminations (CIE), UK and theInternational Baccalaureate Organisation (IBO), Geneva. It was founded by Mrs. Ratna Reddy, an educationist and entrepreneur, and is managed by the CHIREC educational society. The school boasts 3222 students from pre-primary level through class XII, 300 teaching staff and 357 supporting staff. It aims to provide a platform to each individual to develop holistically and help discover inherent talent in the fields of fine art, performing arts, music and sports.', 'Affiliated with CBSE, CIE and IBO, the school offers schooling from pre-primary level through class XII. While CBSE and CIE curricula are offered from the pre-primary level through class XII, the IBDP programme is offered for classes XI and XII.\r\n\r\nThe teacher student ratio is as follows:\r\n\r\nPre-primary-\r\n\r\nIntegrated Curriculum- 1:15\r\n\r\nCambridge- 1:13\r\n\r\nPrimary-\r\n\r\nIntegrated Curriculum- 1:30\r\n\r\nCambridge- 1:26\r\n\r\nThe teaching-learning process encompasses group discussions, panel discussions, seminars and symposium, hands on learning experiences, field trips, projects, demonstrations, guest lectures, and workshops.\r\n\r\nThe first 10 days in the month of June are used for teacher training programmes. The school conducts professional development teachers training program once a month.\r\n\r\nThe distinctive features of the education imparted by CHIREC School are:\r\n\r\n1) Learning that goes beyond the boundaries of a set curriculum.\r\n\r\n2) Equal emphasis on academics and co-curricular activities.\r\n\r\n3) Technology based teaching strategies for effective learning.\r\n\r\n4) Close supervision of curriculum delivery and assessment.\r\n\r\n5) Individual assessment to enhance the studentâ€™s performance.\r\n\r\nExtra-curricular activities:\r\n\r\nBesides academics, the school encourages its students to engage in various outdoor and indoor activities such as basket ball, cricket, hockey, badminton, tennis, skating, gymnastics, volley ball, music, dance, painting, chess and guitar.', 'CHIREC is reckoned among the top international schools in the city of Hyderabad. It strives for holistic development of the childâ€™s personality by laying equal emphasis on academics, co-curricular activities, physical development and creative talents.\r\n\r\nCHIREC International has consistently received recognition from the world\'s leading education magazines. Ranked among the top International Day Schools in the country by Education World Magazine since 2014,  and Digital Learning Magazine. CHIREC has also been routinely accorded with the \"Academic Excellence Award\" by Brainfeed Magazine, and the \"International School Award\" by the British Council.\r\n\r\nIn recent years, CHIREC has been granted the \"ASIAONE Award\"[12] for being the \"Best Brand in Education,\" and NDTV Award for \"Excellence in Sports.\" \r\n\r\nCHIREC received the GLOBE Platinum Award for the â€˜Best Brandâ€™ at the World Business Conclave - Hong Kong in 2016.', 'The school admits maximum number of students at nursery level.\r\n\r\n2. Age eligibility\r\n\r\nClass\r\n\r\nMin. age as on 30th June, 2015\r\n\r\nDate of birth between\r\n\r\nNursery\r\n\r\n2 years 6 months\r\n\r\n1st Jan and 31st Dec 2012\r\n\r\nPre-primary I\r\n\r\n3 years 6 months\r\n\r\n1st Jan and 31st Dec 2011\r\n\r\nPre-primary II\r\n\r\n4 years 6 months\r\n\r\n1st Jan and 31st Dec 2010\r\n\r\nClass I\r\n\r\n5 years 6 months\r\n\r\n1st Jan and 31st Dec 2009\r\n\r\nThe admission process completes by January or latest by February every year.\r\n\r\nFees-\r\n\r\nAnnual Fees for the year 2014 â€“ 15 in INR\r\n\r\nClasses\r\n\r\nCBSE\r\n\r\nCIE\r\n\r\nPre primary\r\n\r\nRs 90,000/-\r\n\r\nRs 1,05,000/-\r\n\r\nPrimary\r\n\r\nRs 1,10,000/-\r\n\r\nRs 1,35,000/-\r\n\r\nSecondary\r\n\r\nRs 1,50,000/-\r\n\r\nRs 1,90,000/-\r\n\r\nSenior secondary\r\n\r\nRs 2,00,000/-\r\n\r\nRs 3,00,000/-', 3222, 375, 6, 'CHIREC Public School', 'This page give info about CHIREC Public School', 122);

